recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Directive 90/219/EEC of 23 April 1990 on the contained use of genetically modified micro-organisms (1), and in particular Article 20 thereof,
Whereas Directive 90/219/EEC classifies genetically modified micro-organisms into two groups having regard to the risks they present, whereas Annex II to the said Directive sets out the criteria for determining such classification;
Whereas, having regard to the experience gained with the contained use of genetically modified micro-organisms, and to technical progress generally in the field of biotechnology, and on the basis of an evaluation of the risks currently presented, it is  appropriate to revise the classification of genetically modified micro-organisms;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Directive are in accordance with the opinion of the Committee established by Article 21 of Directive 90/219/EEC,
